                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d925">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 E.W./9–644: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-06T20:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 6, 1944—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 7—8:44 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5883. Reference my 5751, September 1. Mr. Pilet told me yesterday that he had
                    received an inquiry on behalf of Mussolini as to whether permission could be
                    accorded Mrs. Mussolini to come to Switzerland. Mr. Pilet said he did not see
                    that there could be any objection and that he proposed to give request favorable
                    consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
